Text: The legislation would also require the USPS to create an online dashboard with local and national delivery time data.

The legislation would require retired postal employees to enroll in Medicare when eligible, while dropping a previous mandate that forced the agency to cover its health care costs years in advance.
Those two measures would save the USPS nearly $50 billion over the next decade.

A sweeping bill that would overhaul the US Postal Service's finances and allow the agency to modernize its service is riding a wave of rare bipartisan support.

After clearing the House 342-92 last week, the legislation is headed to the Senate. Finally some constructive work.
